stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> Unchecked

    Unchecked --> Checked : "User interacts (click / space)"
    Checked --> Unchecked : "User interacts (click / space)"

    Unchecked --> DisabledUnchecked : "System sets disabled=true"
    DisabledUnchecked --> Unchecked : "System sets disabled=false"

    Checked --> DisabledChecked : "System sets disabled=true"
    DisabledChecked --> Checked : "System sets disabled=false"

    note left of Unchecked
        **Default State**
        Can transition to:
        - Checked (interaction)
        - DisabledUnchecked (system)
    end note

    note right of Checked
        **Selected State**
        Can transition to:
        - Unchecked (interaction)
        - DisabledChecked (system)
    end note

    note right of DisabledUnchecked
      **Non-interactive States**
      User interactions are ignored.
      Only the system can change state
      by re-enabling the component.
    end note